Job Vacancies Module - Implementation Walkthrough
This document summarizes the complete implementation of the Job Vacancies (Convocatorias) module for the job recruitment system.

Overview
The Job Vacancies module has been successfully implemented following the existing modular architecture pattern. The module enables administrators to create, manage, and publish job vacancies with complex state management, file attachments, and multiple job profiles.

Module Structure
All code is organized in src/Modules/JobVacancies/ following the established pattern:

JobVacancies/
├── Enums/
│   ├── VacancyStatus.php
│   └── ApplicationMode.php
├── Models/
│   ├── JobVacancy.php
│   ├── JobVacancyFile.php
│   ├── JobProfile.php
│   └── JobVacancyEditLog.php
├── Applications/
