Database Schema
Existing migrations (already created):

job_vacancies - Main vacancy table
job_vacancy_files - Attached documents (bases, annexes, corrections)
job_profiles - Job positions within each vacancy
job_vacancy_edit_logs - Audit trail for changes
NOTE

The job_vacancy_files table has a column named job_vancancy_id (with typo) in the migration. The code maintains this typo for consistency with the existing schema.

Key Features Implemented
1. Enums
VacancyStatus
Defines the five states of a job vacancy:

PUBLICADA (1) - Published, allows full editing without logs
CERRADA (2) - Closed to applicants
EN_EVALUACION (3) - In evaluation, restricted editing
FINALIZADA (4) - Finalized, end of life
CANCELADA (5) - Cancelled, end of life
ApplicationMode
SINGLE_PROFILE (0) - Applicant can apply to only one profile (default)
MULTIPLE_PROFILES (1) - Applicant can apply to multiple profiles
2. Models with Business Logic
All models include relationship definitions and business validation methods:

JobVacancy key methods:

isEditable()
 - Checks if vacancy can be edited
canAttachFiles()
 - Verifies file attachment permissions
canUpdateProfiles()
 - Validates profile update permissions
shouldLogChanges()
 - Determines if edit logging is required
canEditOldFileNames()
 - Controls file name editing based on status
3. State Management Rules
The implementation enforces the following business rules:

Status	Edit Data	Edit Profiles	Attach Files	Edit File Names	Log Changes
Publicada	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	❌ No
Cerrada	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	✅ Yes
En Evaluación	❌ No	❌ No	✅ Yes (new only)	❌ No (old files)	✅ Yes
Finalizada	❌ No	❌ No	❌ No	❌ No	N/A
Cancelada	❌ No	❌ No	❌ No	❌ No	N/A
4. Authorization
All protected endpoints use 
RequestContext
 for authorization:

Administrators (with p.admin or p.rrhh permissions) can create/edit vacancies
Users can only edit vacancies from their assigned locale
Public users can list and view published vacancies
5. File Management
Files are stored using Laravel Storage in storage/app/public/job_vacancies/{user_id}/
File types: vacancy attachments (bases, annexes, corrections) and profile descriptions
Display name can be edited separately from actual filename
Automatic cleanup on deletion (service method available)
6. Edit Logging
All changes to vacancies are automatically logged when status ≠ PUBLICADA:

Records: user, timestamp, IP address, action type
Tracks: old values, new values, changed fields
Special handling for status changes (always logged)
API Endpoints
Public Endpoints
List Vacancies

GET /api/job-vacancies
Returns only published vacancies with limited data (no user_id, locale_id)

View Vacancy Details

GET /api/job-vacancies/show?id={id}
Returns complete vacancy details including profiles and files

Download Files

GET /api/job-vacancies/files/download/{filePath}
Public download of vacancy files and profile descriptions

Protected Endpoints (Admin Only)
Create Vacancy

POST /api/job-vacancies
Body: {
  title, status, mode, start_date, close_date,
  profiles: [{ title, salary, office_id, code_profile, file }]
}
Update Vacancy

PATCH /api/job-vacancies
Body: { id, title?, status?, mode?, start_date?, close_date? }
Update Status

PATCH /api/job-vacancies/status
Body: { id, status }
Attach File

POST /api/job-vacancies/files
Body: { job_vacancy_id, file, name }
Update File Name

PATCH /api/job-vacancies/files
Body: { id, name }
Manage Profiles

POST /api/job-vacancies/profiles
Body: {
  job_vacancy_id,
  profiles: [{ id?, title, salary, office_id, code_profile?, file? }]
}
IMPORTANT

All routes use request body parameters (no URL wildcards) as specified by the user.

Implementation Notes
Simplified Design Decisions
Based on user feedback, the implementation was simplified:

No file type classification - State changes handled manually through vacancy updates, not automatic file-based triggers
No separate FileType enum - Keeps the file management simpler
Manual state transitions - Administrators explicitly change status rather than files triggering changes
Consistency with Existing Code
The implementation follows patterns from 
ProfessionalRecords
 module:

DTOs use readonly properties
Repositories include 
findByIdOrFail
 methods
Use cases wrapped in DB transactions
Requests extend 
Template
 with 
verifyPermission()
Controllers use RequestContextResolver::fromRequest()
Known Schema Issue
The migration file 
create_job_vacancy_files_table.php
 contains a typo in the foreign key column: job_vancancy_id instead of job_vacancy_id. The implementation maintains this typo throughout the codebase for database consistency.

Testing
Five comprehensive feature test suites were created (but not executed per user request):

CreateJobVacancyTest - Tests vacancy creation with profiles, validation, and authentication
UpdateJobVacancyTest - Tests updates, edit restrictions by status, and audit logging
ListJobVacanciesTest - Tests public vs admin lists, data filtering, and access control
JobVacancyStatusTest - Tests status transitions and status change logging
JobProfileManagementTest - Tests profile CRUD, file uploads, and validation
Test files location: tests/Feature/JobVacancies/

To run tests (when ready):

bash
php artisan test --filter JobVacancies
